---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Sample Claude Exams, including local browser storage and data handling."
>
  <section class="exam-page legal-page">
    <header class="page-intro">
      <span class="exam-page-eyebrow">Privacy</span>
      <h1 class="exam-page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="section-lede">Last updated July 2, 2026.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="legal-stack">
      <section>
        <h2>What the site stores</h2>
        <p>
          The practice exam uses your browser's local storage to remember active sessions, answers,
          flags, skipped questions, flashcard state, domain history, and optional profile fields you
          type into the save-progress form.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Where that data lives</h2>
        <p>
          In the current static version, that practice data stays in your browser. It is not sent to
          a server by the exam interface. Clearing browser data for this site removes the saved
          progress.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Accounts, payments, and analytics</h2>
        <p>
          This site does not require an account, does not process payments, and does not include a
          built-in analytics tracker in the source code. Hosting providers may still create normal
          operational logs such as IP address, path, user agent, and timestamp.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>External links</h2>
        <p>
          Links to third-party websites are governed by those third parties' policies. This site
          cannot control how external services handle data after you leave Sample Claude Exams.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions, use the contact channel provided by the site owner where this site
          is published.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
